  "text": "The economics of a venture fund are structured so that if you invest at an early stage and, uh, since someone only has an idea or an MVP, each project must have the potential to return a hundred to a thousand times its value. That is to say, the later the stage, the fewer multiples an investor expects as a return. Huh. So, uh, let's say, uh, right now, for instance, uh, a company perhaps like SpaceX, uh, has shares being traded on the private market, meaning, uh, investors are looking to buy and sell these shares, and the return requirements may be two, three, or 4X, just as an example. Uh, but 20 years ago when SpaceX was just starting out, the investor's requirement was no less than 100X.",
